Create a cloud flow with these specifications:

TRIGGER: Manually trigger a flow

VARIABLES TO INITIALIZE (all at the start):
- varWarnings (String, empty)
- varRCCount (Integer, 0)
- varBPCount (Integer, 0)
- varCPNew (Integer, 0)
- varCPUpdated (Integer, 0)
- varCPRemoved (Integer, 0)
- varAppNew (Integer, 0)
- varAppUpdated (Integer, 0)
- varAppDecom (Integer, 0)
- varImportCycleID (String, empty)
- varRCFileID (String, empty)
- varBPFileID (String, empty)
- varCPFileID (String, empty)
- varAppFileID (String, empty)

STEP 1: LIST FILES
- List files in 4 OneDrive for Business folders:
  - /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/ReferenceControls (rename action: List RC Files)
  - /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/BusinessProcesses (rename action: List BP Files)
  - /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/ControlProcedures (rename action: List CP Files)
  - /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/Applications (rename action: List App Files)

STEP 2: CHECK IF ANY FILES EXIST
- Condition: if all 4 folders are empty, terminate with success message "No files to process"
- If at least one folder has a file, continue

STEP 3: CREATE IMPORT CYCLE
- Add a new row in Dataverse table "Import Cycles"
  - Cycle Name: "Import " + current month and year
  - Sync Date: today
  - Status: Draft
  - Triggered By: "Power Automate"
- Set varImportCycleID to the new record's ID

STEP 4: PROCESS REFERENCE CONTROLS
- Condition: if RC folder has files
  - Set varRCFileID to the first file's ID
  - Read the Excel file using Excel Online Business connector, List rows present in a table. Table name is "Referencecontrols"
  - The Excel file has 3 columns: Reference Control ID, Reference Control Title, Reference Control Description
  - For each row in the Excel table:
    - Upsert a row in Dataverse table "Reference Controls" using alternate key on column "Reference Control Identifier" (logical name: pei_referencecontrolidentifier)
      - Reference Control Identifier = Excel column "Reference Control ID"
      - Reference Control Title = Excel column "Reference Control Title" 
      - Reference Control Description = Excel column "Reference Control Description"
      - Lifecycle Status = Active
    - Increment varRCCount by 1
  - Move the file from /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/ReferenceControls to /00.EMS/EMS/Archive/ReferenceControls

STEP 5: PROCESS BUSINESS PROCESSES
- Same pattern as Reference Controls but:
  - Folder: /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/BusinessProcesses
  - Excel table name: "BusinessProcesses"
  - Excel columns: Business Process ID, Process Name, Business Process Owner, Business Process Manager(s)
  - Dataverse table: "Business Processes"
  - Upsert using alternate key on "Business Process Identifier" (logical name: pei_businessprocessidentifier)
    - Business Process Identifier = Excel "Business Process ID"
    - Process Name = Excel "Process Name"
    - Business Process Owner = Excel "Business Process Owner"
    - Business Process Managers = Excel "Business Process Manager(s)"
    - Lifecycle Status = Active
  - Increment varBPCount
  - Archive to /00.EMS/EMS/Archive/BusinessProcesses

STEP 6: PROCESS CONTROL PROCEDURES (most complex - creates Staged Records)
- Same file reading pattern but:
  - Folder: /00.EMS/EMS/Inbox/ControlProcedures
  - Excel table name: "ControlProcedures"
  - Excel columns: Control Procedure ID, Key Control No, Control Procedure Title, Control Procedure Description, Control Procedure Owner, Control Procedure Coordinator, Common Unit, Parent Business Process, Control Procedure Status, Reference Controls, SOX
  - Dataverse table: "Control Procedures"
  - For each row:
    - First check if the Control Procedure already exists in Dataverse by listing rows where pei_controlprocedureidentifier equals the Excel "Control Procedure ID"
    - IF NOT EXISTS (new CP):
      - Add a new row to Control Procedures table with all 11 fields mapped. Lifecycle Status = Active
      - Add a new row to "Staged Records" table:
        - Name = Control Procedure ID from Excel
        - Entity Type = "Control Procedure"
        - Display Title = Control Procedure Title from Excel
        - What Changed = "New"
        - Impact on Evidence = "New Control Procedure. Requires scope classification and applicability mapping."
        - Import Cycle = varImportCycleID
      - Increment varCPNew by 1
    - IF EXISTS (existing CP):
      - Compare the existing Dataverse record's Control Procedure Description and Reference Controls fields with the Excel values
      - IF DESCRIPTION OR REFERENCE CONTROLS CHANGED:
        - Update the row in Control Procedures with all fields
        - Add a new row to Staged Records:
          - What Changed = "Updated"
          - Impact on Evidence = "Description or Reference Control mappings changed. Existing classifications may need review."
          - Import Cycle = varImportCycleID
        - Increment varCPUpdated by 1
      - IF NO KEY FIELDS CHANGED:
        - Update the row silently with all fields (no Staged Record)
  - Archive to /00.EMS/EMS/Archive/ControlProcedures

STEP 7: UPDATE IMPORT CYCLE COUNTS
- Update the Import Cycle row in Dataverse:
  - Reference Controls Imported = varRCCount
  - Business Processes Imported = varBPCount
  - Control Procedures New = varCPNew
  - Control Procedures Updated = varCPUpdated
  - Row ID = varImportCycleID

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- All Dataverse table names use publisher prefix "pei_"
- All Excel files are in OneDrive for Business
- Use Upsert for Reference Controls and Business Processes (simple create/update)
- Use List rows + condition for Control Procedures (need to detect evidence-affecting changes and create Staged Records)
- The Excel files have named tables inside them
- Handle empty rows gracefully - skip any row where the ID column is empty
